Deployment Steps ⚙️
1. Install LAPS

Download and install the LAPS MSI on the Domain Controller and client machines.

Install both Management Tools (for AD integration) and Client (on the workstation).

2. Extend Active Directory Schema
Import-Module AdmPwd.PS
Update-AdmPwdADSchema

3. Set Permissions

Grant read/write access to authorized users:

Set-AdmPwdComputerSelfPermission -OrgUnit "OU=Computers,DC=domain,DC=com"
Set-AdmPwdReadPasswordPermission -OrgUnit "OU=Computers,DC=domain,DC=com" -AllowedPrincipals "IT Support"

4. Configure Group Policy

Open Group Policy Management.

Create or edit a GPO targeting computers where LAPS is needed.

Navigate to:
Computer Configuration → Policies → Administrative Templates → LAPS
Configure:

Enable local admin password management

Password Settings (length, complexity, expiration)

Enable password expiration

5. Verify Deployment
Get-AdmPwdPassword -ComputerName "CLIENT01"


This should return the current local administrator password for the target machine.


